## P1 Relay Pipeline Critical Gaps - Implementation Plan
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:both, module:relay, priority:P0
**Depends on:** G26, G28, G29

### Overview
Comprehensive plan to address the two critical gaps identified in the relay pipeline architecture review (A24-A32): bring_in tool implementation and multi-provider API configuration.

### Phase Breakdown

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P1.1 | Implement BringInTool backend | Coder | 1 day | D24 | draft | Create BringInTool struct in backend/src/forge/tools.rs with JSON schema validation for target, classification, reason parameters. Implement validation: target must exist in ProfessionRegistry and caller's handoff_to list. Deliverable: Tool struct compiles, validation tests pass. |
| P1.2 | Implement HandoffNote struct | Coder | 0.5 day | P1.1 | draft | Create HandoffNote struct in backend/src/forge/mod.rs with fields: from_agent, from_profession, to_profession, classification, summary, warnings. Implement render() method that generates markdown system message. Deliverable: HandoffNote struct with render() method and unit tests. |
| P1.3 | Update Profession registry | Coder | 0.5 day | P1.1 | draft | Add handoff_to and allowed_tools fields to Profession struct in backend/src/relay/profession.rs. Update Assistant profession to include bring_in in allowed_tools and ["advisor", "coder"] in handoff_to. Deliverable: Profession struct updated, default professions loaded correctly. |
| P1.4 | Add SSE agent_handoff event | Coder | 0.5 day | P1.2 | draft | Add agent_handoff event type to ForgeStreamEvent with fields: from_agent, from_profession, to_profession, to_agent, classification, reason. Emit event after successful bring_in execution. Deliverable: SSE event emitted on handoff, frontend receives event. |
| P1.5 | Update ForgeSession handoff logic | Coder | 0.5 day | P1.2, P1.3 | draft | Add active_profession field to ForgeSession. Implement switch_profession() method. Modify forge_stream ReAct loop to inject HandoffNote as system message before next agent turn. Deliverable: Session switches profession correctly, handoff note injected. |
| P1.6 | Create HandoffCard frontend component | Coder | 0.5 day | D24 | draft | Create HandoffCard.vue component with props: from_agent, to_agent, classification, reason. Render arrow icon, agent names, classification badge, reason text with distinct background color. Deliverable: Component renders correctly in chat stream. |
| P1.7 | Update useForge composable | Coder | 0.5 day | P1.4 | draft | Handle agent_handoff SSE event in useForge.ts. Update activeProfession state on handoff. Pass event data to HandoffCard renderer. Deliverable: activeProfession updates, handoff card displays. |
| P1.8 | Update profession badge UI | Coder | 0.5 day | P1.7 | draft | Update ChatView.vue to show current agent name in header badge. Change badge display when agent_handoff event received (Nicole → Isaac). Deliverable: Badge shows correct agent name after handoff. |
| P1.9 | Update Nicole's soul | Planner | 0.5 day | P1.1 | draft | Update .autoforge/souls/assistant.md with bring_in instructions. Add examples: NEW_GOAL → bring_in advisor, REQ_UPDATE → bring_in advisor, DIRECT → bring_in coder. Emphasize autonomous handoff vs suggestions. Deliverable: Nicole's soul includes bring_in instructions. |
| P1.10 | Integration testing | Coder | 0.5 day | P1.1-P1.8 | draft | Write integration tests for bring_in validation, handoff note injection, SSE event emission, and frontend rendering. Test E2E flow: Nicole classifies NEW_GOAL, brings Isaac, Isaac receives context without asking user to repeat. Deliverable: All integration tests pass. |

### Success Criteria
- Nicole autonomously brings Isaac for NEW_GOAL classification in 95%+ of test cases
- HandoffNote prevents "repeat your question" incidents from specialists
- Frontend shows visual handoff transition card with correct styling
- Active profession badge updates correctly in UI
- Zero validation bypasses (handoff_to list enforced)

