## P2 Multi-Provider API Configuration - Implementation Plan
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:both, module:api-sources, priority:P0
**Depends on:** G13, D19, D20, D40

### Overview
Complete the multi-provider API configuration system to enable provider flexibility, cost optimization via 5-tier model system, and automatic provider detection.

### Phase Breakdown

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P2.1 | Implement ApiSource data model | Coder | 0.5 day | D19 | draft | Create ApiSource and ModelDefinition structs in backend/src/relay/config.rs. ApiSource fields: id, name, provider (enum), api_key_env, api_key_stored, base_url, is_available, models. ModelDefinition fields: id, name, tier (ModelTier enum). Deliverable: Structs compile and serialize correctly. |
| P2.2 | Implement ApiSource CRUD operations | Coder | 1 day | P2.1 | draft | Implement load_api_sources(), save_api_sources(), detect_available_providers(), resolve_api_key(), test_connection() functions in backend/src/relay/config.rs. Add file persistence to dirs::data_local_dir()/autoforge/api_sources.json. Deliverable: CRUD operations persist and load correctly. |
| P2.3 | Implement provider auto-detection | Coder | 0.5 day | P2.2 | draft | Scan ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var, ~/.claude/settings.json, OPENAI_API_KEY env var, localhost:11434 for Ollama. Auto-create ApiSource entries with default models per provider (Min/Lite/Mid/Large/Max tiers). Deliverable: Auto-detection finds all configured providers on startup. |
| P2.4 | Implement dispatch_chat() function | Coder | 1 day | D20, P2.1 | draft | Create dispatch_chat() in backend/src/ai.rs with provider-specific URL construction, auth headers, and SSE parsing. Handle Anthropic, OpenAI, and Local providers with their respective SSE formats. Deliverable: dispatch_chat() routes to correct provider, parses SSE correctly. |
| P2.5 | Add CRUD API endpoints | Coder | 0.5 day | P2.2 | draft | Add GET/POST /api/forge/config/api-sources, PUT/DELETE /api/forge/config/api-sources/{id}, POST /api/forge/config/api-sources/{id}/test endpoints in backend. Implement handlers for listing, creating, updating, deleting, and testing API sources. Deliverable: All endpoints return correct responses. |
| P2.6 | Create ApiSourcesView UI | Coder | 1.5 day | P2.5 | draft | Create ApiSourcesView.vue with source list showing provider icons, detail editor for each source, model management table (tier assignment), and Test Connection button. Implement form validation and error handling. Deliverable: UI renders correctly, forms submit valid data. |
| P2.7 | Update AgentConfig resolution | Coder | 1 day | P2.2, P2.6 | draft | Modify useAgentConfigs.ts to resolve AgentConfig.model_tier via ApiSource store instead of hardcoded values. Update agent creation/editing UI to select from available API sources and model tiers. Deliverable: Agent config uses ApiSource-based model resolution. |
| P2.8 | Implement migration from existing keys | Coder | 0.5 day | P2.3 | draft | Add one-time migration on startup that imports existing ANTHROPIC_API_KEY from env or ~/.claude/settings.json into api_sources.json. Show migration notification to user explaining 5-tier system. Deliverable: Existing keys migrated on first run, notification displays. |
| P2.9 | Implement fallback chain logic | Coder | 0.5 day | P2.4 | draft | Update AgentInstance::spawn() to use fallback chain from ModelConfig. Try primary model, on error try fallback models in order, return error if all fail. Log fallback attempts for debugging. Deliverable: Fallback works across providers on API failure. |
| P2.10 | Integration testing | Coder | 1 day | P2.1-P2.9 | draft | Write integration tests for multi-provider dispatch, CRUD persistence, test connection, auto-detection, and fallback chains. Verify tier optimization reduces token costs by >40%. Deliverable: All integration tests pass, cost reduction verified. |

### Success Criteria
- Auto-detects Anthropic, OpenAI, and Local providers on first startup
- Users can configure multiple sources via UI (create, read, update, delete)
- Agents use different providers per model tier (Gofer→Min, Architect→Large)
- Test Connection endpoint validates credentials and returns success/failure
- Fallback chain works across providers on API failure
- Token cost reduction >40% with tier optimization vs single-provider

