## P3 Architecture Status Synchronization - Maintenance Plan
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:docs, module:relay, priority:P1
**Depends on:** G26, G27

### Overview
Implement systematic verification process to keep architecture documents synchronized with implementation status, preventing future documentation drift.

### Phase Breakdown

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P3.1 | Audit architecture documents | Architect | 0.5 day | G27 | draft | Review all 32 architecture documents (A1-A32) for accurate status. Cross-reference with design documents (D1-D40) to verify implementation claims. Create status matrix document showing discrepancies. Deliverable: Complete audit report with status discrepancies identified. |
| P3.2 | Update architecture status fields | Architect | 0.5 day | P3.1 | draft | Update architecture status from draft/approved to implemented where verified. Add "Last Verified" timestamp to each architecture document. Document any intentional deviations from original architecture with rationale. Deliverable: All architecture docs have accurate status and timestamps. |
| P3.3 | Create verification checklist | Architect | 0.5 day | P3.2 | draft | Define checklist for future architecture updates: (1) Cross-reference with design status, (2) Verify implementation against code, (3) Update status field, (4) Add timestamp, (5) Document deviations. Deliverable: Checklist document saved to specs/. |
| P3.4 | Implement CI status check | Architect | 1 day | P3.3 | draft | Add CI check that flags status inconsistencies between architecture and design documents. Parse spec files, extract status fields, compare cross-references, fail build if discrepancy found. Deliverable: CI check runs on spec changes, catches drift. |
| P3.5 | Schedule quarterly audits | Architect | 0.25 day | P3.4 | draft | Add calendar reminder for quarterly architecture review (next: 2025-04-15). Create template for audit report with status matrix, discrepancies found, and updates applied. Deliverable: Recurring audit scheduled, template created. |

### Success Criteria
- 100% of architecture documents match implementation reality
- Zero discrepancies between architecture status and design status
- "Last Verified" timestamp on all architecture documents
- CI check catches status inconsistencies automatically
- Quarterly audit process documented and scheduled

