## P4 Relay Pipeline Optimization - Implementation Plan
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:relay, priority:P2
**Depends on:** G30, G37, G41

### Overview
Implement high-value optimizations to improve observability, reduce token costs, and enhance system resilience after critical gaps are resolved.

### Phase Breakdown

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P4.1 | Driver health monitoring | Coder | 1 day | D29 | draft | Add health check endpoint GET /api/forge/relay/driver/status returning per-run metrics: uptime, token rate, error count, last heartbeat. Implement graceful shutdown on 3 consecutive failures. Add lifecycle event logging (start, pause, resume, crash, recovery). Deliverable: Health endpoint returns metrics, graceful shutdown works. |
| P4.2 | Handoff compression | Coder | 0.5 day | D3 | draft | Compress HandoffDocument.work_product field when > 10KB using zstd compression. Add size hints to HandoffDocument (compressed vs raw). Implement lazy decompression on receiving agent side. Deliverable: Handoff compression reduces size by 20-30%, decompression works. |
| P4.3 | Checkpoint compression | Coder | 0.5 day | D4 | draft | Replace gzip with zstd for checkpoint compression. Store diffs instead of full Ledger state when possible. Add optional external blob storage for checkpoints > 5MB. Deliverable: Checkpoint size reduced by 40-50%, compression faster. |
| P4.4 | Context analytics dashboard | Coder | 2 day | G5 | draft | Create per-agent token tracking: input, output, cumulative. Build cost comparison view: actual vs parallel-swarm estimate. Add visual breakdown by profession (pie chart) and historical trends (30-day sparkline). Implement agent efficiency ranking (tokens per decision). Deliverable: Analytics dashboard shows token spend by agent. |
| P4.5 | Gate timeout configuration | Coder | 0.5 day | D6 | draft | Make polling interval configurable per-gate. Add auto-snooze after N minutes of inactivity. Implement escalation notification for stale gates. Add gate expiration with auto-reject option. Deliverable: Gate timeout configurable, auto-snooze works. |

### Success Criteria
- Driver health endpoint returns metrics for all active runs
- Handoff compression achieves 20-30% token savings for multi-step pipelines
- Checkpoint compression reduces file size by 40-50%
- Context analytics dashboard displays per-agent token breakdown
- Gate timeout configuration prevents forgotten gates from blocking pipelines

