## Implementation Priority Order

### Phase 1: Critical Gaps (P0) - Days 1-12
1. **P1: bring_in Tool** (3 days) - Unblock chat handoff functionality
2. **P2: Multi-Provider** (5 days) - Enable cost optimization via tier system
3. **P3: Architecture Sync** (1 day) - Prevent future documentation drift

### Phase 2: High-Value Optimizations (P2) - Days 13-18
4. **P4: Relay Optimizations** (6 days) - Improve observability and reduce costs

### Phase 3: Future Features (P3) - Days 19-28
5. **P5: Wiki Semantic Search** (4 days) - Improve knowledge retrieval
6. **P6: AutoDown Editor** (5 days) - Better editing experience

---

## Dependencies & Risks

### Critical Path Dependencies
- P1 (bring_in) must complete before P2 (multi-provider) can start
- P3 (architecture sync) can run in parallel with P1/P2
- P4 (optimizations) requires P1/P2 completion
- P5/P6 (future features) no hard dependencies

### Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Impact | Probability | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|
| bring_in validation complexity | Medium | Low | Start with strict validation, relax if too restrictive |
| Multi-provider SSE parsing bugs | High | Medium | Reuse existing provider/ module, add extensive tests |
| Architecture sync reveals more gaps | Low | Medium | Build buffer into timeline for surprise issues |
| Tiptap learning curve delays P6 | Low | Medium | Reuse Novel.sh patterns, allocate extra time |
| FAISS integration complexity | Medium | Low | Start with simple vector search, optimize later |

---

