## P40 Model Tier Refactoring: 3-Tier to 5-Tier Migration
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:both, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** G13, G26, D40, A23

### Overview
Migrate the model tier system from 3 tiers (Light, Mid, Heavy) to 5 tiers (Min, Lite, Mid, Large, Max) to enable finer cost optimization and better alignment with available LLM capabilities.

### Migration Strategy

| Legacy Tier | New Tier | Rationale |
|-------------|----------|-----------|
| Light | Lite | Preserves middle-ground positioning |
| Mid | Mid | Unchanged |
| Heavy | Large | Maps to strong-but-not-maximum models |

- **Min**: Ultra-cheap models for high-volume, low-complexity tasks (Haiku, GPT-4o-mini)
- **Max**: Ultra-strong models for deepest reasoning (future Opus 4, o1)

### Implementation Phases

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P40.1 | Backend: Update ModelTier enum | Coder | 2h | - | draft | Expand ModelTier enum in `backend/src/relay/config.rs` from 3 to 5 variants (Min, Lite, Mid, Large, Max). Add `display_name()`, `description()`, and `order()` methods per D40 §Backend Implementation. Deliverable: enum compiles and all match arms updated. |
| P40.2 | Backend: Implement legacy migration support | Coder | 3h | P40.1 | draft | Add `OldModelTier` enum and `From<OldModelTier> for ModelTier` trait implementation. Create `migrate_api_sources()` function that maps Light→Lite, Mid→Mid, Heavy→Large. Add unit tests for all legacy tier conversions. Deliverable: migration function with 100% test coverage. |
| P40.3 | Backend: Update auto-detection logic | Coder | 2h | P40.1 | draft | Modify `scan_importable_sources()` in `config.rs` to use new 5-tier mappings. Anthropic: Haiku→Min, Sonnet→Lite, Opus→Large. OpenAI: GPT-4o-mini→Min, GPT-4o→Lite, o1-preview→Large, o1→Max. Deliverable: auto-detection returns sources with 5 tiers. |
| P40.4 | Backend: Update agent config defaults | Coder | 2h | P40.1 | draft | Modify `generate_default_agents_with_source()` with new tier assignments per D40 §Agent Config Defaults. Assistant→Lite, Tester→Min, Gofer→Min, Architect/Reviewer→Large, others→Mid. Deliverable: default agents use new tier mappings. |
| P40.5 | Backend: Add migration handler | Coder | 3h | P40.2 | draft | Implement `ensure_migrated()` function that checks for legacy tier values on startup and calls `migrate_api_sources()` if needed. Add to `main.rs` or `lib.rs` initialization. Deliverable: automatic migration on first run. |
| P40.6 | Frontend: Update type definitions | Coder | 1.5h | - | draft | Update `ModelTier` type in `frontend/src/composables/useApiSources.ts` from 3 to 5 variants. Add `TIER_DISPLAY`, `TIER_DESCRIPTIONS`, `TIER_ORDER` constants per D40 §Frontend Implementation. Deliverable: TypeScript types compile. |
| P40.7 | Frontend: Update agent config types | Coder | 1h | P40.6 | draft | Update `AgentConfigDto.model_tier` in `frontend/src/composables/useAgentConfigs.ts` to use new 5-variant type. Deliverable: agent config interface matches backend. |
| P40.8 | Frontend: Update API Sources tier selector | Coder | 2h | P40.6 | draft | Modify tier selector dropdown in `frontend/src/views/ApiSourcesView.vue` to render 5 tier options with labels and descriptions from `getTierOptions()`. Deliverable: UI shows 5 tier choices. |
| P40.9 | Frontend: Update Agents config tier selector | Coder | 2h | P40.6 | draft | Modify tier selector in `frontend/src/views/AgentsConfigView.vue` to use 5-tier options. Add tier hint text showing description. Deliverable: agent config UI supports all 5 tiers. |
| P40.10 | Frontend: Create migration notification component | Coder | 3h | P40.6 | draft | Create `frontend/src/components/MigrationNotification.vue` per D40 §Migration Notification Component. Add localStorage check for `autoforge_tier_version`. Show one-time notification explaining 5-tier system. Deliverable: notification appears on first launch. |
| P40.11 | Frontend: Integrate migration notification | Coder | 1h | P40.10 | draft | Import and render `MigrationNotification` in `App.vue`. Wire up dismiss handler to set localStorage flag. Deliverable: notification displays in app root. |
| P40.12 | Testing: Backend unit tests | Tester | 2h | P40.2, P40.5 | draft | Write unit tests in `backend/src/relay/config.rs` tests module: `test_model_tier_serde()`, `test_migration_from_3tier()`, `test_agent_default_tiers()`. Deliverable: all tests pass with 100% coverage of migration logic. |
| P40.13 | Testing: Integration tests | Tester | 3h | P40.5 | draft | Create integration test that loads legacy `api_sources.json`, verifies migration runs, and confirms new tier values. Test agent creation with new tiers. Deliverable: integration test suite passes. |
| P40.14 | Testing: Frontend component tests | Tester | 2h | P40.8, P40.9 | draft | Write tests for tier selector components verifying 5 options render, labels are correct, and selection persists. Deliverable: component tests pass. |
| P40.15 | Documentation: Update API documentation | Documenter | 2h | P40.1 | draft | Update `specs/apis.ad` with new tier system documentation. Document tier selection guidelines and migration path. Deliverable: API docs reflect 5-tier system. |
| P40.16 | Documentation: User-facing migration guide | Documenter | 2h | P40.10 | draft | Create user-facing migration guide explaining the new tiers, cost benefits, and agent tier assignments. Link from migration notification. Deliverable: migration guide published. |
| P40.17 | Verification: End-to-end testing | Tester | 3h | P40.1-P40.16 | draft | Run full E2E test: backup legacy config, start app, verify migration, check all UI components render 5 tiers, create agents with each tier, verify persistence. Deliverable: E2E test passes. |

### Risk Mitigation

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|------------|
| User confusion about new tiers | Medium | One-time notification + clear descriptions in UI |
| Legacy configs fail to load | High | Serde unknown variant handling + comprehensive migration function |
| Frontend type mismatch | High | Synchronized type updates + TypeScript strict mode validation |
| Agent defaults become suboptimal | Low | Reviewed mappings based on task complexity |
| Breaking changes for existing users | High | Automatic migration + backup recommendation in notification |

### Success Criteria

- ✅ Backend ModelTier enum has 5 variants (Min, Lite, Mid, Large, Max)
- ✅ Legacy 3-tier configs automatically migrate to 5-tier on startup
- ✅ All agent default configurations use appropriate new tiers
- ✅ Frontend UI components render 5 tier options with descriptions
- ✅ Migration notification appears once for existing users
- ✅ All unit and integration tests pass with >90% coverage
- ✅ E2E verification confirms migration works without data loss
- ✅ API documentation updated with 5-tier system

